<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-331-537  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 331 537.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Feb 13 1989 v11 n7 p46(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>How managers get the right machines into the right users' hands.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>LaPlante, Alice.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microcomputer managers have come up with a number of ways toallocate equipment within their organizations, but users with thelatest technology often have it only because of clout.andP;  This is aproblem because it means that the most powerful equipment may notbe in the hands of those who can use it to the greatest advantage.andO;One way microcomputer managers can ensure that technology isappropriately distributed is to allocate microcomputers by jobfunction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     User ClassificationInformation Resources ManagementMicrocomputersEnd UsersResource Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>